Table 2: The QA performance evaluation on the out-of-domains of the MRQA benchmark. All models used 
are pretrained on the human-labeled training set from the source domains, and the QA models are finetuned on 
synthetic data generated based on the unannotated passages of the target domains. The finetuned QA models are 
evaluated on human-generated evaluation data for each target domains with the exact match (EM) and F1 scores. 
MMI stands for maximum mutual information inference, EM stands for involving difficult questions with EM 
selection, and CST stands for cooperative self-training.
